{"key":"post-6727480","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6727480</id>\n<content>It should be noted that if you're using karo, you don't need to sterilize at all.  Mrs rabbit has a jar of Karo that she's been using for nearly a year, opening it in the kitchen and sometimes leaving it open for the whole time she's cooking and it has zero contamination in it.  When I say don't microwave LC, I'm referring to using malt extract/yeast, which should be PC'd for half an hour.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As for distilled water for syringe making, as agar said, a good filtered lid is the key, so anything that makes the water boil to kill off bacteria is going to work.  Personally, I pc mine.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6728350</next>\n<prev>6727378</prev>\n<first>6726043</first>\n<last>6753322</last>\n<when>1175268008</when>\n<utime>03/30/07 06:20 PM</utime>\n</post>"}